The deceased were involved in a head on collision on Saturday, leading to the cars catching fire. JOHANNESBURG - The bodies of six Limpopo road users who perished along the R37 road outside Lebowakgomo have finally been identified.The deceased were involved in a head-on collision on Saturday, leading to the cars catching fire.Authorities says the occupants of the vehicles burnt beyond recognition and had their next of kin assist in identifying their bodies.One of them was a 28-year-old female police constable.Police spokesman Motlafela Mojapelo said, All six deceased have been identified with the help of their next of kin. Their bodies were in an unrecognisable state and that is where the assistance from the next of kin came in handy. 